00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:04,396
CHAPTER I. HUTSA PORPOISE.DWILD PORPOISE.

2
00:00:05,337 --> 00:00:08,100
This is the common porpoise found almost all over the globe.

3
00:00:08,781 --> 00:00:15,409
The name is of my own bestowal, for there are more than one sort of porpoises, and something must be done to distinguish them.

4
00:00:15,669 --> 00:00:27,743
I call him thus because he always swims in hilarious shoals, which upon the broad sea keep tossing themselves to heaven like caps in a Fourth of July crowd.

5
00:00:27,723 --> 00:00:31,409
Their appearance is generally hailed with the delight by the mariner.

6
00:00:31,830 --> 00:00:37,419
Full of fine spirits, they invariably come from the breezy billows to windward.

7
00:00:38,020 --> 00:00:40,805
They are the lads that always lived before the wind.

8
00:00:41,346 --> 00:00:43,089
They are accounted a lucky omen.

9
00:00:43,349 --> 00:00:49,399
If you yourself can withstand three cheers at beholding these vivacious fish, then heaven help ye.

10
00:00:49,439 --> 00:00:53,967
The spirit of godly gamesomeness is not in ye.

11
00:00:53,947 --> 00:01:04,484
A well-fed plump Huzzah porpoise will yield you one good gallon of good oil, but the fine and delicate fluid extracted from his jaws is exceedingly valuable.

12
00:01:05,305 --> 00:01:08,250
It is in request among jewelers and watchmakers.

13
00:01:09,112 --> 00:01:10,714
Sailors put it on their hones.

14
00:01:11,455 --> 00:01:13,278
Porpoise meat is good eating, you know.

15
00:01:13,318 --> 00:01:17,004
It may never have occurred to you that a porpoise spouts.

16
00:01:17,285 --> 00:01:21,051
Indeed, his spout is so small that it is not very readily discernible.

17
00:01:22,027 --> 00:01:27,535
But the next time you have a chance, watch him, and you will then see the great Sperm Whale himself in miniature.

18
